feedback_text.text: I think it's a bit of a mistake to have every single example provided with an explanation box - at the start of the experiment, I have no idea how much any sperk eats, so I have no real explanation in the initial stages, leaving me feeling a bit frustrated as to what to type; Perhaps splitting that segment up into two would make more sense - a segment that just shows a type of sperk and how much food it ate, and then another segment that -then- asks for explanations, so participants have something they can go off of with the example segment, at least.
